    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Describe your issue\r\n\r\nC file generated by Cython contains a lot of defined macros. Some of them are expected to be used by users to finetune compilation process - e.g. `__PYX_EXTERN_C` - https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/5040#discussion_r980296238\r\n\r\nI have created a PR for mentioning this macro in documentation #5366. But we are missing separate section in Source Files and Compilation documentation providing list of macros with explanation.\r\n\r\nThere are two motivation for doing this:\r\n1. to improve documentation (of course)\r\n2. to explicitly define public \"API\" otherwise we will loose control which macro should be used and which is \"internal\" (and can be changed anytime)\r\n",
    "closed_at": null,
